<p>yesterday I made english muffins from your <a href="http://smittenkitchen.com/2007/01/four-breakfasts/" rel="nofollow">pancakes, english muffins, frisee salad</a> post. They&#8217;re tricky because the dough is so sticky.  The first four were badly burnt.  They set off the smoke alarms.  So I lowered the temp on the griddle to about pancake heat and halved the dough for the next batch.  When they were browned nicely on both sides I thought they were still uncooked in the middle, but&#8230; I was wrong.  Split with a fork and toasted, they were heavenly.</p>
