				<p>I&#8217;ve just finished baking a batch of these moments ago. My dough looked exactly as your refrence picture in the comments above, and I had no problems at all (maybe those who found theirs to be too dry were using smaller eggs? I did use particually large ones..). I ended up rolling out my cookies between plastic wrap, which worked very well for me. And because I&#8217;m using an Aga (which aways runs a little hot, even using the cooling plate) decreased the baking time by 2 mins and turned them around after the first 3. Mine didn&#8217;t rise as much as yours (hardly at all, actually) but turned out with a lovely texture.</p>
