<li class="commentbody" id="comment-561868">
			<cite>Phyllis Katzen</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-561868" title="">January 22, 2011</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">215</div>

				<p>I think i have a helpful hint. Instead of rolling the scraps out over and over on flour and worry about them getting too hard from all the flour, i rolled them out once on a floured board, then took the scraps and put them between a large piece of folded over cellophane, then rolled over the cellophane, nothing sticks, roller is clean. I did roll the scraps together and put back in frig. to harden up before i rolled each batch, but it worked well.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-562950">
			<cite>Naomi</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-562950" title="">January 24, 2011</a> 

		
