				<p>I made these for the first time this weekend, and I too ran into the problem of a slightly crumbly dough (it certainly did NOT look like your picture). I&#8217;m not sure what caused the consistency to be this way (maybe my hand mixer?), but I found that working the dough with my hands (in small portions) helped it to hold together. I was then able to roll it and cut the cookies. I also found that underbaking them  slightly helped to give them the a chewy texture, although they didn&#8217;t seem to be as soft as you described&#8230;luckily my 3 year-old nephew loved them anyway!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
