			<div class="commentcount">288</div>

				<p>Couldn&#8217;t wait for a response. Made them tonight. AMAZING. Will certainly be making these again.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-2076486">
			<cite>Chris</cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-2076486" title="">August 5, 2012</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">289</div>

				<p>Fantastic website! You are just the person for my long standing question. Some 30 yrs ago when I was in HS the &#8220;lunch Ladies&#8221; made their own cookies. I will never forget them and to this day have never had one like it. they were chewy chocolate brownie cookies. They looked like they were baked in a muffin top pan. they were so dense that you could hold the cookie in the palm of your hand, make a fist and the cookie would actually stay formed with ridges that show your finger joints and peaks that divided your fingers. I have not been able to find the right ingredients to make cookies so dense and pliable with such chocolatey goodnes. I hope my description was able to do justice to such goodness. Thank you for your wonderful contributions to comfort food. YUM!</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
<li class="commentbody" id="comment-2076505">
